This paper focuses on using deep pre-trained language models to assist in the training of a text-to-speech system, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as transfer learning and attention-based models, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper also discusses the use of BERT, a popular language model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper involves the development of a state-of-the-art TTS system, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
